line_1: Poor, worthless elf, it eats a dinner,
Full hardly earneth Mat. his Dinner.
line_2: Now sure as Priest did e'er shrive Sinner,

line_1: Unless they gather 't in a dish, at dinner.
line_2: I'll never give a groat, as I'm a sinner,

line_1: I'll ne'er forego my sport or dinner.
line_2: And call me bird, or call me sinner,

line_1: Will sarra us aw at dinner.
line_2: Our cheese hes fill'd the rimmer;

line_1: Was that he sometimes spoilt a dinner;

line_1: Newport-Pannel receiv'd me, and gave me a dinner,
line_2: And a bed at Northampton was press'd by a sinner:
To make the girl a sinner.

line_1: I let you go without a Dinner.
line_2: Yet, if you prove me there a Sinner,

Gae somewhere else and seek your dinner,
